%S A391425 148,229,257,404,733,761,788,916,1028,1076,1229,1373,1396,1489,1492,
%T A391425 1556,1901,2089,2213,2228,2557,2677,2708,2713,2777,2804,2836,2857,
%U A391425 2917,2932,3028,3044,3221,3229,3316,3508,3877,3889,3988,4001,4481,4493,4597,4649,4729,4852,4916,4933
%N A391425 Positive discriminants of orders of quadratic fields with form class number 3.
%C A391425 Not to be confused with A344409, the positive discriminants of orders of quadratic fields with class number 3.
%C A391425 Let h(D) and h+(D) be respectively the class number and the form class number of discriminant D. Since h+(D) = h(D) if the fundamental unit has norm -1 and 2*h(D) otherwise, this sequence consists of D such that h(D) = 3 and that the fundamental unit has norm -1.
%C A391425 Note that the form class group has 2-rank omega(|D|) - t, where omega = A001221, and t = 0 if 32|D, t = 2 if D == 4 (mod 16), t = 1 otherwise (see A391441). As a result, this sequence is exactly the terms in A344409 that are of the form 8, p or 4*p for prime p == 1 (mod 4).
%H A391425 Jianing Song, <a href="/A391425/b391425.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A391425 Rick L. Shepherd, <a href="https://www.digitalgreensboro.org/record/14435">Binary quadratic forms and genus theory</a>, Master of Arts Thesis, University of North Carolina at Greensboro, 2013.
%o A391425 (PARI) QFBclassno(D) = qfbclassno(D) * if (D > 0 && quadunitnorm(D) > 0, 2, 1)
%o A391425 isA391425(n) = n%4 <= 1 && !issquare(n) && QFBclassno(n) == 3 \\ quadunitnorm() requires PARI-GP of version 2.15 or higher
%Y A391425 Cf. A306638 (norms of fundamental units of orders of real quadratic fields).
%Y A391425 For a list of sequences related to the class numbers of real quadratic fields, see A087048.
%K A391425 nonn
%O A391425 1,1
%A A391425 _Jianing Song_, Dec 09 2025
